<F P=105>  French; </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Aerospatiale-Missiles' new facility for testing 
air-breathing engines is now up and running in Bourges. The 
facility was constructed as part of France's "PREPHA" hypersonic 
propulsion research program, and rounds out the three, already 
existing lines for testing ramjet missile applications. The 
facility will be used to validate the operation of large 
engines--up to flight Mach numbers of nearly 7--on the ground. 
The first tests of the PREPHA program scramjet will be conducted 
there in May 1994. The new test line can now compete with the 
best of those in the United States and Russia, and will be a 
driving force in future European efforts to work together on 
hypersonic propulsion. 

