  [Unattributed article: "Alenia Takes Shares in Eisys, a 
Joint Thomson-CSF and EIS Venture"] 
  [Text] Via its Alenia branch, the Italian group 
FINMECCANICA [Mechanical Engineering Finance Corporation] has 
taken a stake in the Eisys Co., a joint venture created at Rome 
in 1992 by Thomson-CSF and Elettronica Ingegneria Sistemi (EIS 
SpA [joint stock company]). The new equity holdings will be: 
Thomson-CSF (37.5 percent and EIS SpA (25 percent). For 
Alenia/FINMECCANICA and for Thomson-CSF, Eisys is a valuable 
partner for the building of data processing systems for European 
FSAF (Future Surface-to-Air Family) anti-air systems in which 
Thomson-CSF and Aerospatiale participate for France and Alenia 
for Italy under the EUROSAM [expansion unknown] venture. 

</TEXT>

