<F P=106> [Article by Philippe Rose: "Bull Grows 21.3 Percent"] </F>
  [Text] Is Bull on the road to recovery? If quarterly 
figures are to be believed, the French group posted an increase 
of 21.3 percent (6.2 billion French francs [Fr]) in consolidated 
sales for the first quarter. Bull management expects "strong 
improvement" in its earnings for the same period. Total growth 
"has greatly surpassed predictions," indicating "the first signs 
of recovery," the group's executive committee said. 
  The Bull Overseas regional area shows the strongest growth, 
with a 37-percent jump in sales, while Bull Europe (+9 percent) 
and Bull North America (+5 percent) have simply reversed 
direction. Bull's microcomputing division increased its revenues 
70 percent, including 132 percent for Zenith Data Systems in the 
United States. Total orders for hardware and software grew 27 
percent, notably as a result of big system orders from the 
Pays-de-Loire Caisse d'Epargne in France and General Electric 
Information Systems in the United States. 

</TEXT>

