  [Text] Siemens has decided to invest 300 million German 
marks in the production of semiconductors in its 
Ratisbonne-based plant (Germany), where the Dram 1's and 4 Mbits 
and logical circuits in 1 micron technology are being produced. 
Jurgen Knorr, head of the German group's semiconductor 
division, had recently announced that the company considered 
expanding one of its existing sites, on top of the planned 
investments in Dresden, in the former GDR. Siemens is planning 
to construct a new production unit in Ratisbonne, which will 
mainly develop logic circuits, thus creating around 200 jobs. 
Production at the new unit could start in mid-1995. 

